{
  "texts": [
    "16 Similarly, a grasp on which events fall within what Ford (2018) describes as the \"province of human agency\" allows us to rule out cases that go beyond what individual agents can accomplish and be held responsible for.",
    "Returning to Anscombe's example: in the case of the man pumping water, the end is a state of affairs his action is aimed at bringing about.",
    "The whole action is a means to get a change in government.",
    "The further consequences involved in this being, from the man's own perspective and the one we take in interpreting him, external to the action since they no longer have the kind of means-end structure revealed by the question 'Why?'",
    "directed towards an individual."
  ]
}